01:32:06.000 --> 01:32:07.270
There are two ways you can represent

01:32:07.280 --> 01:32:09.189
this. One is you can just concat

01:32:09.199 --> 01:32:11.270
everything into a flat vector. The

01:32:11.280 --> 01:32:12.790
problem is that this doesn't capture

01:32:12.800 --> 01:32:15.189
order invariance. So like it's a totally

01:32:15.199 --> 01:32:16.709
different obs if I switch the order of

01:32:16.719 --> 01:32:19.510
this one and this one. Um that's a

01:32:19.520 --> 01:32:22.229
really bad property to have. The other

01:32:22.239 --> 01:32:23.590
thing you can do is you can build some

01:32:23.600 --> 01:32:25.910
sort of entity representation where like

01:32:25.920 --> 01:32:28.310
you concat your embedding or your

01:32:28.320 --> 01:32:30.229
features with the features of every

01:32:30.239 --> 01:32:33.350
other agent. So it's like me and agent

01:32:33.360 --> 01:32:35.030
one, me and agent two, me and agent

01:32:35.040 --> 01:32:38.149
three, so on so on and so forth. You put

01:32:38.159 --> 01:32:40.310
this into an embedding layer. So each of

01:32:40.320 --> 01:32:43.430
these gets embedded separately

01:32:43.440 --> 01:32:45.510
and then you need to do a maximum over

01:32:45.520 --> 01:32:47.910
the entities. The problem with this is

01:32:47.920 --> 01:32:50.550
this applies massive memory pressure

01:32:50.560 --> 01:32:53.669
because you get the embedding dimension

01:32:53.679 --> 01:32:55.350
for every single entity instead of just

01:32:55.360 --> 01:32:58.470
once per OBS. So the trick is that you

01:32:58.480 --> 01:32:59.750
send it through a lowdimensional

01:32:59.760 --> 01:33:01.350
bottleneck. So you only have a

01:33:01.360 --> 01:33:04.310
16dimensional encoding per entity with a

01:33:04.320 --> 01:33:06.950
relu and then you project the 16 dim

01:33:06.960 --> 01:33:09.270
back up to 128 and you fuse a max

01:33:09.280 --> 01:33:12.470
operation. If you do this you get the

01:33:12.480 --> 01:33:14.470
memory pressure of 16 times the number

01:33:14.480 --> 01:33:16.629
of entities but you don't get the memory

01:33:16.639 --> 01:33:18.550
pressure of 128 times the number of

01:33:18.560 --> 01:33:21.669
entities because of the fused max op.

